256
00:15:31.500 --> 00:15:33.041
I'm full up on family.

257
00:15:34.333 --> 00:15:35.416
Yeah. I got you.

258
00:15:37.625 --> 00:15:39.226
Think about that barbecue.

259
00:15:39.250 --> 00:15:41.250
I make a hell of a kebab.

260
00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.041
Morning.

261
00:16:01.541 --> 00:16:02.916
Morning. love.

262
00:16:07.708 --> 00:16:11.476
I thought I might go up to that good
farmer's market at Logan square today.

263
00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:15.166
Yeah. I need shallots for dinner tonight.

264
00:16:19.833 --> 00:16:21.250
So come with me.

265
00:16:22.458 --> 00:16:24.208
I was gonna work on the car.

266
00:16:26.458 --> 00:16:28.083
You and that car.

267
00:16:31.083 --> 00:16:35.083
What is the point of fixing
up a car if you can't drive it?

268
00:16:46.583 --> 00:16:48.017
Yeah. baby!

269
00:16:48.041 --> 00:16:49.041
We got it!

270
00:17:09.375 --> 00:17:12.541
Oye cómo va. mi ritmo

271
00:17:16.208 --> 00:17:17.625
perfect.

272
00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:20.000
Who are these people?

273
00:17:26.541 --> 00:17:28.934
I found his wife's obituary.

274
00:17:28.958 --> 00:17:32.184
- Who?
- Our new neighbor.

275
00:17:32.208 --> 00:17:35.184
Samuel Darwin Cooper.

276
00:17:35.208 --> 00:17:37.642
Born Chicago. Illinois.

277
00:17:37.666 --> 00:17:40.226
December 10. 1953.

278
00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:42.642
You gotta stop stalking people.

279
00:17:42.666 --> 00:17:44.041
I'm not stalking.

280
00:17:44.708 --> 00:17:46.392
I'm investigating.

281
00:17:46.416 --> 00:17:48.351
You're not a reporter anymore.

282
00:17:48.375 --> 00:17:49.851
Journalist.

283
00:17:49.875 --> 00:17:51.559
And that makes it stalking.

284
00:17:51.583 --> 00:17:55.184
His wife died of a
stroke five months ago.

285
00:17:55.208 --> 00:17:56.892
Gosh. She was young.

286
00:17:56.916 --> 00:17:58.642
Not even 70.

287
00:17:58.666 --> 00:18:00.017
Worked for northrop grumman.

288
00:18:00.041 --> 00:18:04.642
Thirty-five years as an
aeronautical engineer.

289
00:18:04.666 --> 00:18:06.517
So we know he's smart.

290
00:18:06.541 --> 00:18:10.017
"Education is not the
learning of the facts.

291
00:18:10.041 --> 00:18:12.392
but the training of the mind to think."

292
00:18:12.416 --> 00:18:13.434
Who said that?

293
00:18:13.458 --> 00:18:14.541
Einstein.

294
00:18:15.291 --> 00:18:17.101
No. maybe Mr. Peabody.

295
00:18:17.125 --> 00:18:19.125
One or the other. I don't remember.

296
00:18:19.625 --> 00:18:22.541
Art? I was thinking we
should go for a walk today.

297
00:18:23.458 --> 00:18:28.434
Your doctors say you need exercise.
real exercise. not the bendy-bendy stuff.

298
00:18:28.458 --> 00:18:30.666
I can't. I'm playing golf with Maximo.

299
00:18:32.291 --> 00:18:34.476
Well. are we still on for a film tonight?

300
00:18:34.500 --> 00:18:37.017
Dog day afternoon is
playing at the palace.

301
00:18:37.041 --> 00:18:38.934
I'm sorry. I forgot.

302
00:18:38.958 --> 00:18:42.333
Loser buys dinner. and Max
always loses. so. you know…

303
00:18:43.125 --> 00:18:45.017
So. hey to Maximo.

304
00:18:45.041 --> 00:18:46.559
Okey dokey.

305
00:18:46.583 --> 00:18:48.875
See you later.

306
00:18:52.208 --> 00:18:53.333
Yeah.

307
00:18:55.708 --> 00:18:56.708
Boy.

308
00:19:19.083 --> 00:19:20.559
No!

309
00:19:20.583 --> 00:19:22.625
Fuck! Fuck!

310
00:19:28.458 --> 00:19:31.517
There he is! Sam the man!

311
00:19:31.541 --> 00:19:33.434
Look. I just wanted to apologize.

312
00:19:33.458 --> 00:19:36.851
- I came on a little strong last night.
- I can't talk now. Jack.

313
00:19:36.875 --> 00:19:41.351
Sure. sure. sure. We can talk about
that whole barbecue shindig later.

314
00:19:41.375 --> 00:19:43.309
There's no rush on that.

315
00:19:43.333 --> 00:19:44.934
Nice wheels. by the way.

316
00:19:44.958 --> 00:19:47.375
Yeah. there's nothing like an icon.

317
00:19:47.875 --> 00:19:51.708
I got a '23. I… now. that's a beaut!

318
00:20:00.083 --> 00:20:02.250
Love the flames. hot stuff!

319
00:20:08.041 --> 00:20:10.767
Young Marcus Shaw was
working in the local coal mine

320
00:20:10.791 --> 00:20:14.392
when he first imagined a town
just for retirees back in 1949.

321
00:20:14.416 --> 00:20:16.101
Everyone thought he was crazy.

322
00:20:16.125 --> 00:20:19.226
but at that very first open
house. the line of cars…

323
00:20:19.250 --> 00:20:21.601
They featured
state-of-the-art appliances.

324
00:20:21.625 --> 00:20:23.767
like the brand-new we sting house oven.

325
00:20:23.791 --> 00:20:26.309
which you can see to your left right here.

326
00:20:26.333 --> 00:20:29.184
We have something special.

327
00:20:29.208 --> 00:20:30.559
You guys come around.

328
00:20:30.583 --> 00:20:31.916
This right here…

329
00:20:32.416 --> 00:20:34.291
We can make that work.

330
00:20:36.583 --> 00:20:37.833
Shouldn't be a problem.

331
00:20:38.541 --> 00:20:39.541
Yes.

332
00:20:40.125 --> 00:20:41.166
That's right.

333
00:20:41.875 --> 00:20:43.684
Thank you for calling the boroughs.

334
00:20:43.708 --> 00:20:45.750
where you'll have the time of your life.

335
00:20:46.291 --> 00:20:47.934
Can I help you. sweetie?

336
00:20:47.958 --> 00:20:49.601
Yeah. my name's Sam Cooper.

337
00:20:49.625 --> 00:20:51.392
I need to speak to Mr. Shaw.

338
00:20:51.416 --> 00:20:52.851
What is this in regards to?

339
00:20:52.875 --> 00:20:54.434
Getting out of my contract.

340
00:20:54.458 --> 00:20:56.625
Well. that's a new one.

341
00:20:57.208 --> 00:20:59.750
Unfortunately. Mr. Shaw
isn't in the office today.

342
00:21:00.416 --> 00:21:01.875
Let me check his schedule.

343
00:21:13.291 --> 00:21:16.833
You're in luck. I can squeeze
you in at 2:00 P.M. on Wednesday.

344
00:21:17.333 --> 00:21:18.333
Do you want it?

345
00:21:21.583 --> 00:21:24.017
Lilly. where are the shallots I asked for?

346
00:21:24.041 --> 00:21:25.166
Shit!

347
00:21:25.666 --> 00:21:26.892
I forgot!

348
00:21:26.916 --> 00:21:29.184
I can't cook chimichurri without shallots.

349
00:21:29.208 --> 00:21:30.976
- Use onions!
- You can't be serious.

350
00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:32.875
Well. they're basically the same.

351
00:21:33.458 --> 00:21:34.978
I'm gonna pretend you didn't say that.

352
00:21:37.333 --> 00:21:39.892
Hey. that's me. and I want you only

353
00:21:39.916 --> 00:21:41.851
- what are you doing?
- Dance with me.

354
00:21:41.875 --> 00:21:43.226
I have to cook dinner.

355
00:21:43.250 --> 00:21:44.250
It can wait.

356
00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:47.708
- This isn't gonna work.
- Yeah?

357
00:21:49.125 --> 00:21:50.767
We both know that isn't true.

358
00:21:50.791 --> 00:21:52.184
Pork chops are gonna burn.

359
00:21:52.208 --> 00:21:54.684
Don't be such a grump.

360
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:59.392
So you're scared. and you're
thinking that maybe we ain't that young…

361
00:21:59.416 --> 00:22:00.892
…anymore

362
00:22:00.916 --> 00:22:05.017
show a little faith
there's magic in the night

363
00:22:05.041 --> 00:22:08.500
you ain't a beauty but hey. you're all right

364
00:22:09.708 --> 00:22:13.541
and that's all right with me

365
00:22:15.333 --> 00:22:19.142
you can hide 'neath your
covers and study your pain

366
00:22:19.166 --> 00:22:22.958
make crosses from your
lovers throw roses in the rain.

367
00:22:25.083 --> 00:22:26.208
Lilly?

368
00:22:27.541 --> 00:22:28.541
Lilly!

369
00:22:30.500 --> 00:22:31.666
Lilly!

370
00:22:32.333 --> 00:22:33.333
Lilly!

371
00:22:34.208 --> 00:22:36.250
Look at me. honey! Lilly!

372
00:22:36.833 --> 00:22:38.666
Mr. Cooper. are you all right?

373
00:22:42.666 --> 00:22:44.000
Yeah. I'm fine.

374
00:22:47.666 --> 00:22:48.666
I'm sorry.

375
00:22:52.083 --> 00:22:54.083
You look like you've seen a ghost.

376
00:22:54.791 --> 00:22:55.833
I have to go. Sorry.

377
00:22:57.041 --> 00:22:58.875
Did you want that appointment?

378
00:23:08.666 --> 00:23:10.083
Mickey mantle!

379
00:23:12.375 --> 00:23:14.875
- Nice shot.
- Sun got in my eyes.

380
00:23:20.166 --> 00:23:21.976
All right. new guy.

381
00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:24.934
When we get in there.
let me do the talking.

382
00:23:24.958 --> 00:23:26.416
This lady's a handful.

383
00:23:27.208 --> 00:23:28.291
Comprende?

384
00:23:37.291 --> 00:23:39.059
Looking good. everyone.

385
00:23:39.083 --> 00:23:41.476
Diane? Ooh. that's nice.

386
00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:43.226
Sheila. don't use your hands.

387
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:44.684
Use the pliers. okay?

388
00:23:44.708 --> 00:23:46.541
Then you can get right in there.

389
00:23:47.458 --> 00:23:48.559
No!

390
00:23:48.583 --> 00:23:51.267
No. no. no. Absolutely not.

391
00:23:51.291 --> 00:23:56.226
I specifically told the seraphim
thing to send anybody but you.

392
00:23:56.250 --> 00:23:57.916
Anybody but chief rent-a-slop.

393
00:23:59.083 --> 00:24:00.267
What can we do. Renee?

394
00:24:00.291 --> 00:24:01.934
I've been robbed. Again.

395
00:24:01.958 --> 00:24:05.476
And… what are we missing this time?

396
00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:07.517
A bag of Rose quartz.

397
00:24:07.541 --> 00:24:09.434
What's that? Expensive?

398
00:24:09.458 --> 00:24:11.142
No. it's like ten bucks.

399
00:24:11.166 --> 00:24:14.809
But I know that I put them on the
shelf in the storage room last night.

400
00:24:14.833 --> 00:24:16.559
and this morning. they were gone.

401
00:24:16.583 --> 00:24:18.809
So somebody broke in and stole them.

402
00:24:18.833 --> 00:24:22.208
Any sign of a break-in?

403
00:24:22.708 --> 00:24:25.226
- No.
- Of course not.

404
00:24:25.250 --> 00:24:26.601
Look. nothing we can do.

405
00:24:26.625 --> 00:24:28.333
We could file a report.

406
00:24:28.833 --> 00:24:33.726
- Yes. yes. Thank you…
- paz. -Thank you. paz.

407
00:24:33.750 --> 00:24:36.000
Let's do that. Let's take a report.

408
00:24:38.250 --> 00:24:43.208
You know. last week. Meredith
stidwell reported her car stolen.

409
00:24:43.916 --> 00:24:48.226
Turns out… she loaned it
to her daughter and forgot.

410
00:24:48.250 --> 00:24:50.684
It just happens all the
time in folks your age.

411
00:24:50.708 --> 00:24:52.392
You know. look around.

412
00:24:52.416 --> 00:24:55.517
I mean. you got stones worth
a lot more than ten bucks here.

413
00:24:55.541 --> 00:24:58.642
You misplaced your quartz and forgot it.

414
00:24:58.666 --> 00:25:01.184
Just like Meredith stidwell.

415
00:25:01.208 --> 00:25:03.208
and just like the last time you called.

416
00:25:03.791 --> 00:25:08.601
The worst thing I could do
for you is file a report that says.

417
00:25:08.625 --> 00:25:12.291
"confused old woman is confused again."

418
00:25:13.541 --> 00:25:14.541
You're welcome.

419
00:25:31.541 --> 00:25:33.559
- What do you call it?
- Brentwood.

420
00:25:33.583 --> 00:25:35.559
What do you do here nights?

421
00:25:35.583 --> 00:25:36.767
They eat their dinner.

422
00:25:36.791 --> 00:25:39.892
They all come here
and eat the big dinner.

423
00:25:39.916 --> 00:25:42.333
You're a pretty bright boy. aren't you?

424
00:25:43.375 --> 00:25:44.416
Well...

425
00:25:52.333 --> 00:25:53.500
Jesus!

426
00:26:03.333 --> 00:26:04.333
Stop!

427
00:26:04.916 --> 00:26:06.250
- What?
- Just stop.

428
00:26:07.375 --> 00:26:08.833
Just give me a damn minute.

429
00:26:21.541 --> 00:26:22.601
You a mechanic?

430
00:26:22.625 --> 00:26:23.767
Engineer.

431
00:26:23.791 --> 00:26:25.250
Close enough.

432
00:26:26.416 --> 00:26:27.476
I'm Renee.

433
00:26:27.500 --> 00:26:28.851
Sam.

434
00:26:28.875 --> 00:26:30.916
- New guy on the block.
- I guess.

435
00:26:32.000 --> 00:26:33.250
Try the engine.

436
00:26:33.958 --> 00:26:35.642
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

437
00:26:35.666 --> 00:26:37.458
All right.

438
00:26:44.416 --> 00:26:46.583
Whoa! Thank you.

439
00:26:48.166 --> 00:26:49.166
Hey!

440
00:26:50.875 --> 00:26:52.851
Hey! I'm trying to thank you!

441
00:26:52.875 --> 00:26:55.101
I don't want it. I just want some sleep.

442
00:26:55.125 --> 00:26:56.666
Well then. say you're welcome.

443
00:26:57.625 --> 00:26:58.791
Excuse me?

444
00:26:59.541 --> 00:27:00.601
Here's a tip.

445
00:27:00.625 --> 00:27:05.101
When somebody says "thank
you." you just say "you're welcome"

446
00:27:05.125 --> 00:27:07.267
instead of being a snippy little bitch.

447
00:27:07.291 --> 00:27:09.267
The other person will go on their way.

448
00:27:09.291 --> 00:27:13.767
and you can go back to doing
what all grumpy old men love to do.

449
00:27:13.791 --> 00:27:14.791
Be alone.

450
00:27:18.166 --> 00:27:19.166
You're welcome.

451
00:27:20.083 --> 00:27:21.250
Attaboy. Sam.

452
00:28:07.583 --> 00:28:08.666
Who the hell are you?

453
00:28:09.875 --> 00:28:10.958
Shit.

454
00:28:11.458 --> 00:28:12.351
Where's grace?

455
00:28:12.375 --> 00:28:14.541
Take it easy. buddy.

456
00:28:16.250 --> 00:28:17.250
It's in the walls.

457
00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:19.517
- What is?
- The owl.

458
00:28:19.541 --> 00:28:20.541
Owl?

459
00:28:21.958 --> 00:28:24.476
This is all wrong. Where's grace?

460
00:28:24.500 --> 00:28:27.791
Wait. Wait. wait. wait.
Grace. She used to live here?

461
00:28:28.291 --> 00:28:30.267
You're her husband? I can help you.

462
00:28:30.291 --> 00:28:32.892
No. I have to find the door.

463
00:28:32.916 --> 00:28:34.809
We can find the door together.

464
00:28:34.833 --> 00:28:37.666
Just put the knife down.

465
00:28:38.833 --> 00:28:40.642
You're one of them.

466
00:28:40.666 --> 00:28:42.017
Where's grace?

467
00:28:42.041 --> 00:28:43.851
You took her! Where is she?

468
00:28:43.875 --> 00:28:46.583
You've got her! You give her back!

469
00:28:47.708 --> 00:28:50.226
- Give her back. dammit!
- Stop it!

470
00:28:50.250 --> 00:28:52.892
- Give her back!
- I don't have her. you psycho!

471
00:28:52.916 --> 00:28:53.916
Give her back!

472
00:28:58.041 --> 00:28:59.375
Help. somebody!

473
00:29:00.208 --> 00:29:01.267
Somebody. help!

474
00:29:01.291 --> 00:29:02.601
Help!

475
00:29:02.625 --> 00:29:03.517
Calm down!

476
00:29:03.541 --> 00:29:05.059
Edward. that's enough!

477
00:29:05.083 --> 00:29:07.642
No. no. no. He's one of them.

478
00:29:07.666 --> 00:29:10.458
- Time to go home.
- But this is my home.

479
00:29:12.541 --> 00:29:14.208
No! Gracie!

480
00:29:18.625 --> 00:29:20.851
All patched up. Lucky
you didn't need stitches.

481
00:29:20.875 --> 00:29:22.517
Yeah. that's me. Mr. Lucky.

482
00:29:22.541 --> 00:29:25.476
- How we doing over here?
- He is good as new.

483
00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:27.601
I wouldn't go that far.

484
00:29:27.625 --> 00:29:30.184
Well. I realize you had a rough morning.

485
00:29:30.208 --> 00:29:31.934
Don't want to take up your time.

486
00:29:31.958 --> 00:29:36.934
But you need anything. call security.
you ask for Hank. I'll get you sorted.

487
00:29:36.958 --> 00:29:38.226
What about the police?

488
00:29:38.250 --> 00:29:42.517
Well. legally speaking.
the boroughs isn't a town.

489
00:29:42.541 --> 00:29:44.309
It's all unincorporated land.

490
00:29:44.333 --> 00:29:47.767
They set it up that way so the
company doesn't have to provide schools

491
00:29:47.791 --> 00:29:49.934
or… police departments.

492
00:29:49.958 --> 00:29:53.851
Now. there's a county sheriff. but
those boys are stretched pretty thin.

493
00:29:53.875 --> 00:29:56.601
so we try not to sweat
'em with the small stuff.

494
00:29:56.625 --> 00:29:58.500
Small stuff? A man broke into my house.

495
00:29:59.083 --> 00:30:00.809
- I'm sorry.
- I was attacked.

496
00:30:00.833 --> 00:30:03.892
- I understand.
- Apparently. you do not understand.

497
00:30:03.916 --> 00:30:05.309
Maybe the sheriff will.

498
00:30:05.333 --> 00:30:09.059
Look. Mr. Cooper. no
one is gonna stop you

499
00:30:09.083 --> 00:30:11.684
from calling the sheriff
if you're dead set on it.

500
00:30:11.708 --> 00:30:14.226
But there's someone
you should talk to first.

501
00:30:14.250 --> 00:30:16.642
- Who's that?
- My boss.

502
00:30:16.666 --> 00:30:18.041
Blaine Shaw.

503
00:30:20.708 --> 00:30:22.750
Fine. But I call shotgun.

504
00:30:23.250 --> 00:30:24.666
Can't allow that. Sorry.

505
00:30:40.541 --> 00:30:43.083
- I thought I was meeting the boss.
- You are.

506
00:30:45.791 --> 00:30:48.226
- What is this place?
- The manor.

507
00:30:48.250 --> 00:30:51.416
It's where they stick the potatoes.
Like your little visitor today.

508
00:30:57.958 --> 00:31:00.642
- Some door.
- We take security seriously here.

509
00:31:00.666 --> 00:31:02.892
Yeah? How'd the guy
who attacked me get out?

510
00:31:02.916 --> 00:31:04.392
We're still figuring that out.

511
00:31:04.416 --> 00:31:07.125
But I assure you. it won't happen again.

512
00:31:13.875 --> 00:31:16.892
Apparently. all this helps
folks suffering from dementia.

513
00:31:16.916 --> 00:31:18.851
Makes them feel at home.

514
00:31:18.875 --> 00:31:20.226
Kind of trippy. right?

515
00:31:20.250 --> 00:31:21.267
That it is.

516
00:31:21.291 --> 00:31:24.392
- Mr. Shaw's waiting for you in the café.
- Café?

517
00:31:24.416 --> 00:31:27.125
We'll be out front to take
you home when you're done.

518
00:31:32.166 --> 00:31:34.726
Excuse me. Do you have the time?

519
00:31:34.750 --> 00:31:37.017
- It's almost 10:00.
- Good.

520
00:31:37.041 --> 00:31:39.750
Then I haven't missed my bus.

521
00:31:41.583 --> 00:31:43.458
Mrs. Taylor?

522
00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:46.809
There we go.

523
00:31:46.833 --> 00:31:48.625
Oops. Sorry.

524
00:31:49.291 --> 00:31:50.708
Hold on.

525
00:31:52.958 --> 00:31:54.625
Just a second. There…

526
00:31:55.125 --> 00:31:56.434
There we are.

527
00:31:56.458 --> 00:31:57.916
Pretty as a picture.

528
00:31:58.416 --> 00:31:59.809
Mr. Cooper.

529
00:31:59.833 --> 00:32:02.309
Hello. I'm Blaine Shaw.
ceo of the boroughs.

530
00:32:02.333 --> 00:32:04.434
I know who you are. I've seen you on TV.

531
00:32:04.458 --> 00:32:07.767
Of course. Thank you for
agreeing to meet with me.

532
00:32:07.791 --> 00:32:10.642
Would you like a cold drink? We
have a soda machine. various juices.

533
00:32:10.666 --> 00:32:12.017
No. I'm not thirsty.

534
00:32:12.041 --> 00:32:13.601
Well. please have a seat.

535
00:32:13.625 --> 00:32:14.875
No. I'll stand.

536
00:32:20.791 --> 00:32:21.791
Thank you.

537
00:32:23.708 --> 00:32:27.726
First things first. I owe
you an apology. Mr. Cooper.

538
00:32:27.750 --> 00:32:30.601
It is my responsibility to
keep our residents safe.

539
00:32:30.625 --> 00:32:34.267
and I failed you. and
for that. I am very sorry.

540
00:32:34.291 --> 00:32:36.351
- Yeah. I don't want your apology.
- No.

541
00:32:36.375 --> 00:32:37.833
You want out of your contract.

542
00:32:38.416 --> 00:32:39.517
How do you know?

543
00:32:39.541 --> 00:32:42.583
Well. I heard about what happened
with your transition manager

544
00:32:43.166 --> 00:32:45.059
and with my receptionist.

545
00:32:45.083 --> 00:32:46.517
It's my town. Mr. Cooper.

546
00:32:46.541 --> 00:32:49.684
Nothing goes on around
here without my knowing. so…

547
00:32:49.708 --> 00:32:52.476
I took the Liberty of
speaking with financing.

548
00:32:52.500 --> 00:32:54.684
Had the proper documents drawn up.

549
00:32:54.708 --> 00:32:56.416
Provided I don't call the sheriff.

550
00:32:57.208 --> 00:32:58.375
That's right.

551
00:32:58.958 --> 00:33:00.059
Yeah. fine with me.

552
00:33:00.083 --> 00:33:02.517
There is. one more thing.

553
00:33:02.541 --> 00:33:03.767
What?

554
00:33:03.791 --> 00:33:05.833
Edward would like to apologize.

555
00:33:07.166 --> 00:33:08.166
Edward?

556
00:33:13.125 --> 00:33:17.267
Don't worry. He's properly medicated.
He's no harm to anyone. I can assure you.

557
00:33:17.291 --> 00:33:19.416
Yeah. I'll keep my distance. all the same.

558
00:33:23.208 --> 00:33:24.250
Edward?

559
00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:28.750
Edward? Can you hear me?

560
00:33:29.583 --> 00:33:31.267
Is it time for supper?

561
00:33:31.291 --> 00:33:35.601
No. not yet. but there's
somebody here to see you.

562
00:33:35.625 --> 00:33:36.916
Gracie?

563
00:33:37.791 --> 00:33:40.875
No. no. It's… it's Mr. Cooper.

564
00:33:41.458 --> 00:33:45.000
Do you remember what we
talked about? About Mr. Cooper?

565
00:33:45.791 --> 00:33:47.851
Yes. Yes.

566
00:33:47.875 --> 00:33:50.809
Mr. Cooper… I'm sorry. Mr. Cooper.

567
00:33:50.833 --> 00:33:52.458
I am sorry.

568
00:33:56.791 --> 00:33:58.291
Well done. Edward.

569
00:34:02.375 --> 00:34:04.851
What's wrong with him? Alzheimer's?

570
00:34:04.875 --> 00:34:06.101
Maxwell's.

571
00:34:06.125 --> 00:34:08.434
It's a rare neurological disease.

572
00:34:08.458 --> 00:34:11.375
It causes the brain to
literally wither and die.

573
00:34:11.875 --> 00:34:14.208
There's no cure. no treatment.

574
00:34:14.708 --> 00:34:18.517
Edward and the world are locked in a
race to see who can forget the other first.

575
00:34:18.541 --> 00:34:20.642
What about friends. family?

576
00:34:20.666 --> 00:34:25.375
Edward and grace had a son. Joey.
but sadly. he passed quite young.

577
00:34:26.166 --> 00:34:29.351
No. the manor is all Edward has now.

578
00:34:29.375 --> 00:34:30.750
Like everyone here.

579
00:34:32.041 --> 00:34:35.851
Well. I think we have taken up
quite enough of your time. Mr. Cooper.

580
00:34:35.875 --> 00:34:38.517
You are on to bigger and better things.

581
00:34:38.541 --> 00:34:39.934
So here's your contract.

582
00:34:39.958 --> 00:34:42.416
All that's left for you to do is sign.

583
00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:44.666
Of course.

584
00:34:45.166 --> 00:34:46.767
you could always stay.

585
00:34:46.791 --> 00:34:49.101
Now. I… I realize it's a long shot.

586
00:34:49.125 --> 00:34:52.500
We haven't exactly put
our best foot forward. but…

587
00:34:54.166 --> 00:34:57.166
Well. I know what you've lost. Sam.

588
00:34:58.208 --> 00:35:02.000
And I suspect you don't
have anywhere to go.

589
00:35:02.958 --> 00:35:03.958
Do you?

590
00:35:06.791 --> 00:35:11.017
You know. loneliness is a
disease just as savage as Maxwell's.

591
00:35:11.041 --> 00:35:13.458
And far more common these days.

592
00:35:14.666 --> 00:35:17.583
But nobody's ever alone in the boroughs.

593
00:35:20.708 --> 00:35:21.875
Well…

594
00:35:25.583 --> 00:35:27.708
Maybe I'll just have a lawyer look at it

595
00:35:29.041 --> 00:35:30.267
before I sign.

596
00:35:30.291 --> 00:35:32.434
Well. that's very wise. Mr. Cooper.

597
00:35:32.458 --> 00:35:33.958
You take your time.

598
00:35:34.541 --> 00:35:36.351
Not too much. though.

599
00:35:36.375 --> 00:35:40.916
As my wife likes to remind me. time
is a precious commodity around here.

600
00:36:13.375 --> 00:36:14.833
Sam the man.

601
00:36:18.291 --> 00:36:20.809
Everything hunky-dory?

602
00:36:20.833 --> 00:36:23.934
I saw the wambulances
in front of your place today.

603
00:36:23.958 --> 00:36:27.041
- Got me worried.
- All good. False alarm.

604
00:36:27.958 --> 00:36:31.642
Glad to hear. Yeah.

605
00:36:31.666 --> 00:36:34.726
Yeah. I… I just stopped by because…

606
00:36:34.750 --> 00:36:37.875
Well. you know. I was
thinking about that barbecue.

607
00:36:38.541 --> 00:36:40.041
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

608
00:36:44.208 --> 00:36:46.375
Thinking anything in particular?

609
00:36:48.166 --> 00:36:51.250
Yeah. I was thinking. you know. maybe…

610
00:36:51.958 --> 00:36:53.708
It's not such a bad idea.

611
00:36:54.333 --> 00:36:57.059
You know. maybe I should…

612
00:36:57.083 --> 00:36:59.208
Yeah. maybe I should
meet the neighbors.

613
00:37:00.041 --> 00:37:01.416
Makes sense.

614
00:37:02.125 --> 00:37:04.226
- How's Thursday?
- No good. no.

615
00:37:04.250 --> 00:37:06.083
Friday would work.

616
00:37:08.250 --> 00:37:09.916
I'll make a few calls.

617
00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:14.000
Yeah.

618
00:37:31.791 --> 00:37:33.476
- Hey. Claire bear.
- Hey.

619
00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:35.059
I have a favor to ask.

620
00:37:35.083 --> 00:37:38.351
Do you have mom's vinyl of
born to run? I was like Ella's age...

621
00:37:38.375 --> 00:37:39.559
yeah.

622
00:37:39.583 --> 00:37:40.976
I can't really talk now.

623
00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:42.851
The neighbor's throwing me a barbecue.

624
00:37:42.875 --> 00:37:46.851
- And you're going?
- Well. you don't have to sound so shocked.

625
00:37:46.875 --> 00:37:50.559
No. I'm not at all surprised
by your sudden popularity.

626
00:37:50.583 --> 00:37:52.166
Yeah. All right. all right.

627
00:37:52.833 --> 00:37:54.267
Bye-bye. butterfly.

628
00:37:54.291 --> 00:37:55.601
See you soon. raccoon.

629
00:37:55.625 --> 00:37:57.208
And don't forget about Bruce.

630
00:37:57.708 --> 00:37:59.309
- What?
- Mom's record.

631
00:37:59.333 --> 00:38:01.184
All right. I'll find it.

632
00:38:01.208 --> 00:38:02.291
Gotta go.

633
00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:15.517
I have stage-four prostate cancer.

634
00:38:18.208 --> 00:38:19.934
I probably don't have much time left.

635
00:38:19.958 --> 00:38:22.517
It seems a waste to spend
it standing outside a party.

636
00:38:22.541 --> 00:38:25.226
Not that I'd call six people in
a backyard much of a party.

637
00:38:25.250 --> 00:38:27.017
but sadly. it's as close as I get

638
00:38:27.041 --> 00:38:29.541
since they banned me
from the community center.

639
00:38:30.250 --> 00:38:31.767
Cowards.

640
00:38:31.791 --> 00:38:32.875
I'm Sam.

641
00:38:33.375 --> 00:38:34.375
Wally.

642
00:38:37.666 --> 00:38:41.291
- You gonna stand out here all night. Sam?
- I'm not very good at parties.

643
00:38:42.041 --> 00:38:44.083
My wife was the sociable one.

644
00:38:44.833 --> 00:38:47.125
People only liked me
when I was with her.

645
00:38:48.500 --> 00:38:51.333
Well. I'm beloved.

646
00:38:52.625 --> 00:38:53.958
So stick close.

647
00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:59.684
And that's the part people
don't want to talk about.

648
00:38:59.708 --> 00:39:01.184
The documents.

649
00:39:01.208 --> 00:39:04.351
You can make fun of them hillbillies
seeing swamp gas all you want.

650
00:39:04.375 --> 00:39:09.291
but then you've got to explain
Nathan twining's 1947 memo. right?

651
00:39:09.875 --> 00:39:11.476
Absolutely. art.

652
00:39:11.500 --> 00:39:12.976
Absolutely.

653
00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:15.142
Look who I found loitering out front.

654
00:39:15.166 --> 00:39:16.351
There he is.

655
00:39:16.375 --> 00:39:17.767
Sam the man.

656
00:39:17.791 --> 00:39:19.392
- Good to see you.
- I brought some beer.

657
00:39:19.416 --> 00:39:23.142
That's great. That's great. Let
me introduce you to the gang here.

658
00:39:23.166 --> 00:39:26.017
- We got art and Judy here.
- How's it going?

659
00:39:26.041 --> 00:39:28.392
- They live next door to you.
- Here. I'll take this.

660
00:39:28.416 --> 00:39:30.767
And you come to me
if you need anything.

661
00:39:30.791 --> 00:39:33.976
Because I have my finger
on the pulse of this place here.

662
00:39:34.000 --> 00:39:35.059
What pulse?

663
00:39:35.083 --> 00:39:37.101
Wally. You obviously met him.

664
00:39:37.125 --> 00:39:40.559
- And the mighty Renee.
- Yeah. we met.

665
00:39:40.583 --> 00:39:44.476
That's fantastic. All right. Well.
let's all get down to business.

666
00:39:44.500 --> 00:39:46.226
Go in there. grab your plates.

667
00:39:46.250 --> 00:39:48.309
Just because Carlos castaneda lied

668
00:39:48.333 --> 00:39:51.351
about everything that he did
doesn't mean what he meant...

669
00:39:51.375 --> 00:39:53.892
so. Jack. which lucky widow

670
00:39:53.916 --> 00:39:56.601
are you sending into
peaks of ecstasy this week?

671
00:39:56.625 --> 00:39:58.351
Whoo! Careful. Wally.

672
00:39:58.375 --> 00:40:00.642
We both know you're the
only man in the boroughs

673
00:40:00.666 --> 00:40:02.892
with a higher body count than mine.

674
00:40:02.916 --> 00:40:04.684
What? He's damn right.

675
00:40:04.708 --> 00:40:09.101
By the way. I was monogamous
15 years after 9/11. so…

676
00:40:09.125 --> 00:40:10.601
I hate that term. "body count."

677
00:40:10.625 --> 00:40:11.976
You're right.

678
00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:13.625
What would you call it?

679
00:40:14.208 --> 00:40:15.250
My "back catalogue."

680
00:40:16.958 --> 00:40:20.142
- That's good. I like that.
- Right? It's better. Yeah.

681
00:40:20.166 --> 00:40:21.642
How are you settling in?

682
00:40:21.666 --> 00:40:23.017
Fine.

683
00:40:23.041 --> 00:40:24.291
Couple of bumps.

684
00:40:26.125 --> 00:40:28.142
Did you know grace and Edward?

685
00:40:28.166 --> 00:40:29.476
Yeah.

686
00:40:29.500 --> 00:40:32.017
Grace and I used to play tennis together.

687
00:40:32.041 --> 00:40:33.851
She was a hoot.

688
00:40:33.875 --> 00:40:35.059
What about Edward?

689
00:40:35.083 --> 00:40:36.142
Edward?

690
00:40:36.166 --> 00:40:37.226
He was a dick.

691
00:40:37.250 --> 00:40:39.791
It's about bringing people together.

692
00:40:41.750 --> 00:40:45.101
This is blue dream.

693
00:40:45.125 --> 00:40:48.851
A hybrid sativa. Tastes like sweet berries.

694
00:40:48.875 --> 00:40:51.184
No. no. no. I'll pass.

695
00:40:51.208 --> 00:40:52.767
You still on the vape?

696
00:40:52.791 --> 00:40:54.059
It's healthier.

697
00:40:54.083 --> 00:40:55.434
Ha-ha!

698
00:40:55.458 --> 00:40:59.000
I tried weed salsa the other day.

699
00:40:59.625 --> 00:41:00.851
Unnecessary.

700
00:41:00.875 --> 00:41:03.166
They put weed in everything now.

701
00:41:03.666 --> 00:41:06.750
I have weed tiger balm for arthritis.

702
00:41:07.250 --> 00:41:09.559
It smells of licorice.

703
00:41:09.583 --> 00:41:13.184
Some people hate
the aroma. but I love it.

704
00:41:13.208 --> 00:41:17.017
No. I don't think I'd better do that.
I'm going in for surgery tomorrow.

705
00:41:17.041 --> 00:41:19.184
Jack. Is it the gout?

706
00:41:19.208 --> 00:41:20.934
Are you gonna have a toe removed?

707
00:41:20.958 --> 00:41:22.142
No. no. no.

708
00:41:22.166 --> 00:41:23.791
I'm having a mole cut off.

709
00:41:24.708 --> 00:41:27.809
What? Come on. Getting a
mole sliced off does not count.

710
00:41:27.833 --> 00:41:29.017
- It counts.
- No.

711
00:41:29.041 --> 00:41:31.684
No. I'm a retired doctor. It doesn't count.

712
00:41:31.708 --> 00:41:34.017
I had my spine fused.

713
00:41:34.041 --> 00:41:37.351
Now. that is surgery. Here. here.

714
00:41:37.375 --> 00:41:39.309
- Look at this.
- He's gonna show.

715
00:41:39.333 --> 00:41:41.083
Yeah. take a look at this.

716
00:41:42.083 --> 00:41:42.976
There it is.

717
00:41:43.000 --> 00:41:45.833
All right. You know what?
That ain't nothing. Sorry.

718
00:41:46.583 --> 00:41:49.625
I had a whole new hip installed.

719
00:41:50.125 --> 00:41:51.958
- Right?
- Amazing.

720
00:41:52.791 --> 00:41:55.601
Okay. y'all gonna have to
imagine my c-section scar.

721
00:41:55.625 --> 00:41:57.267
Aw. where's the fun in that?

722
00:41:57.291 --> 00:41:59.434
Show us what you're
working with. playboy.

723
00:41:59.458 --> 00:42:01.208
All my scars are emotional.

724
00:42:01.791 --> 00:42:05.041
I'm afraid to say I think I got you all beat.

725
00:42:05.541 --> 00:42:07.392
Check it out.

726
00:42:07.416 --> 00:42:09.351
God. they cracked your chest.

727
00:42:09.375 --> 00:42:10.767
They went in twice.

728
00:42:10.791 --> 00:42:15.559
Ladies and gentlemen.
we have a winner!

729
00:42:15.583 --> 00:42:17.458
Just saying.

730
00:42:18.666 --> 00:42:22.000
How about you. new guy?
You got any battle scars?

731
00:42:23.041 --> 00:42:24.125
My retina detached.

732
00:42:25.458 --> 00:42:26.767
Your retina detached?

733
00:42:26.791 --> 00:42:27.791
Yeah.

734
00:42:29.625 --> 00:42:30.684
Like in a bar fight?

735
00:42:30.708 --> 00:42:34.333
No. I woke up one morning. I
couldn't see out of my left eye.

736
00:42:34.916 --> 00:42:36.142
Apparently. it's genetic.

737
00:42:36.166 --> 00:42:38.642
Happened to my dad when
he was about the same age.

738
00:42:38.666 --> 00:42:41.392
We all become our fathers.

739
00:42:41.416 --> 00:42:43.267
The worst thing. they took my license.

740
00:42:43.291 --> 00:42:47.101
Elders should be respected
and venerated. They treat us like…

741
00:42:47.125 --> 00:42:48.642
- Yeah. like children.
- Yes.

742
00:42:48.666 --> 00:42:50.601
- We should start a revolution.
- Yes.

743
00:42:50.625 --> 00:42:52.601
- Yeah.
- To the grey rebellion!

744
00:42:52.625 --> 00:42:55.392
To the grey rebellion!

745
00:42:55.416 --> 00:42:58.333
The grey rebellion!

746
00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:07.416
Lilly!

747
00:43:08.041 --> 00:43:10.726
Look at me! Look at me!

748
00:43:10.750 --> 00:43:11.684
Help!

749
00:43:11.708 --> 00:43:13.583
Somebody help!

750
00:43:15.083 --> 00:43:16.226
Judy!

751
00:43:16.250 --> 00:43:18.684
- Judy. Hold on! Judy!
- Shit!

752
00:43:18.708 --> 00:43:21.392
- You have to hold her from behind.
- You're gonna be okay.

753
00:43:21.416 --> 00:43:24.017
Hold on. I'll get her a glass of water.

754
00:43:24.041 --> 00:43:25.809
Good. good.

755
00:43:25.833 --> 00:43:27.517
It's all right. I got her.

756
00:43:27.541 --> 00:43:29.226
- You sure?
- Come on. baby. You all right?

757
00:43:29.250 --> 00:43:31.267
- Thank god.
- Come on. Sit down.

758
00:43:31.291 --> 00:43:32.434
Sit down.

759
00:43:32.458 --> 00:43:34.375
There you go. All right. babe.

760
00:43:43.375 --> 00:43:48.125
Fuck you! Fuck! Fuck
you! Fucking piece of shit!

761
00:43:49.750 --> 00:43:50.750
Fuck.

762
00:43:55.458 --> 00:43:56.916
My wife is dead.

763
00:44:00.333 --> 00:44:01.833
I'm sorry. buddy.

764
00:44:13.500 --> 00:44:14.791
My wife's dead.

765
00:44:17.916 --> 00:44:19.767
And the world just keeps on turning.

766
00:44:19.791 --> 00:44:22.726
and people just keep on living their lives.

767
00:44:22.750 --> 00:44:26.583
They shop. and they…
laugh. and they eat.

768
00:44:27.333 --> 00:44:30.976
And they go to sleep. and they
get up. and they do it all over again.

769
00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:32.416
And I hate 'em for it!

770
00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:35.333
My wife is dead.

771
00:44:37.625 --> 00:44:38.666
Yeah.

772
00:44:41.791 --> 00:44:43.625
My second wife. she…

773
00:44:44.791 --> 00:44:46.559
Read a lot of self-help books.

774
00:44:46.583 --> 00:44:49.166
Not that they helped her much. but…

775
00:44:50.375 --> 00:44:52.041
That's beside the point.

776
00:44:52.833 --> 00:44:55.625
I remember this one
thing that she told me once.

777
00:44:56.541 --> 00:45:02.291
Grief makes your past feel
too close and your future

778
00:45:03.041 --> 00:45:04.267
too far away.

779
00:45:04.291 --> 00:45:06.601
Well. my wife's dead.
